@node "General" "Instructions   "
@toc "Instructions"
Control is via the mouse.  To make @{"Bud" link "Bud" 0} walk, move the mouse pointer to where
you want Bud to walk to, and click the @{fg shine}left@{fg text} mouse button.

The icons in the control screen (pictures of keys, a mouth, etc) are @{"verbs" link "Verbs" 0};
click on a @{"verb" link "Verbs" 0}, and then an object, and Bud will perform the action on the
object.  For example, if you clicked on the Operate button, and then on an
airlock, Bud would open the airlock and space himself, to avoid being included
in yet another poor adventure game.  Needless to say, this puzzle is not
included in the game, because we didn't want to draw the explosion.

To use a verb, click on the appropriate icon with the @{fg shine}left@{fg text} button, and then
the object with the @{fg shine}right@{fg text} button.  Otherwise, Bud will simply walk over to it.
An object is either:

 - A thing in a room, eg. a table
 - A word in the inventory (the large blue window in the control panel).

Move the mouse over the object or word, and its name will appear in the blue
strip at the top of the control panel.
@endnode

@node "Verbs" "Verbs          "
@toc "Instructions"
The verb icons are as follows:

@{b}@{u}EXAMINE (an eye)@{ub}@{uu}

Bud walks over and describes an object.


@{b}@{u}TAKE (an upwards-pointing arrow)@{ub}@{uu}

Take an object.


@{b}@{u}OPERATE (an arrow pushing a button)@{ub}@{uu}

Operate a single object.  Also opens doors.


@{b}@{u}USE (an arrow pushing a key into a hole)@{ub}@{uu}

Use one object on another.  The first object is usually held in Bud's
inventory.  It can also can be used to give an object to another character.

@{b}@{u}
TALK TO (a mouth)@{ub}@{uu}

Talk to another character.


@{b}@{u}SHOOT (a gun)@{ub}@{uu}

Shoots something.
@endnode

@node "Load" "Load/save games"
@toc "Instructions"
To save a game, press @{fg shine}SHIFT@{fg text} and @{fg shine}F1@{fg text} - @{fg shine}F10@{fg text}.  Each function key selects a
different save game slot; there are, therefore, 10 slots available.  Press
either the left mouse button to confirm the save, or the right mouse button to
cancel.

To load a game, press @{fg shine}F1@{fg text} - @{fg shine}F10@{fg text}, and then the mouse in the same way as above.
If a saved game is not found, the game currently in progress will continue as
normal.



@{b}@{u}Notes@{ub}@{uu}

A saved game can be loaded at any time, but saving is not allowed during a
cut-scene (when the player has no control over Bud).

Make sure you have not got @{fg shine}Caps Lock@{fg text} enabled; the computer will think you are
pressing @{fg shine}SHIFT@{fg text}, and will save a game instead of loading it.  Frustrating.
@endnode

@node "Other commands" "Other commands "
@toc "Instructions"
The following can be pressed at any time in the game:

   M        -     Memory remaining

   V        -     GRACPlayer version number

   Q        -     Quit (left mouse confirms, right mouse cancels)

   Ctrl C   -     Quit (no confirm necessary)
@endnode

@node "Hints" "Helpful Hints  "
@toc "Instructions"
Examine everything.  This will give vital clues as to the object's use, if it
has one.  There are plenty of @{"red herrings" link "Secrets" 0} about, eg. @{"false leads" link "Secrets" 0}, useless
objects (1200 motherboard revision 1d.4), but all of the puzzles are logical.
The key to success, apparently, is to think like John.

               @{b}@{fg shine}DO NOT DO THIS IF YOU VALUE YOUR SANITY.@{ub}@{fg text}

We have had no reports of anyone suddenly exhibiting symptoms of
multiple-personality disorder, schitzophrenia or manic depression, but this
doesn't mean that it hasn't happened.

You have been warned.
@endnode

